We had so much fun @lacasablanca for the screening of the new movie Flamin’ Hot 🥵 . It was such an honor to get invited and be joined by community leaders from across the nation. It was even more special since it happened during the anniversary #DACA & the National Immigrant Heritage Month. This movie was so encouraging and it tells the story of a LATINO who never gave up on the American Dream. @lindayvettechavez and @evalongoria  DID 👏THAT 👏🔥Huge S/O to @natimont and Emma for thinking of me 🤍 Also, my plus one was pretty cool I guess 🤷🏻‍♀️😒😂🤍 #DACA #thewhitehouse #lacasablanca #moviescreening #flaminhot #movienight

So beto and I took a leap of faith and we bought a building in the DFW area… It’s been a couple of weeks since we got the keys and we’ve been working our butts off to start this new journey. I can’t thank y’all enough for all the messages, emails and text messages with encouraging words. Although, this has been a dream of mine for the longest seeing it happen is mind blowing 😭 As a DACA recipient I feel the need to show you guys that it is possible for us to be successful and that our DREAMS can become a reality if we work hard and keep going 🇲🇽🔥 I know for a fact God deserves all the credit because even with all our hard works he opened doors for us where we never thought it would be possible 🥹😭 Cheers to lots of work and success 🥂 stay tuned 🫶🏼 #newproject  #2023 #daca #smallbusinessowner #building #comingsoon #sisepuede
